// @trap :9:0
// `__trap__("reason")` → stream the reason to the host boundary through the
// print-of-string path (`__print_char__` … `__print_str_flush__`), THEN
// `unreachable`. The abort still maps to this source location, so the wasm
// runner pins only the LOCATION here (its trap message carries the mapped trap
// reason, not the printed text). The printed reason is asserted end-to-end via
// the native `vl run` (see the PR body). The trailing print must never run.
const x = 1
__trap__("boom: invariant violated")
print(x)
